1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:08,040
[The Age of Awakening]

2
00:00:08,040 --> 00:00:11,071
[Episode Thirty-eight]

3
00:00:11,360 --> 00:00:12,320
Given the current potential danger of this career,

4
00:00:12,388 --> 00:00:14,948
[Zhou Enlai, styled Xiangyu, Member of the Tianjin Awakening Society]

5
00:00:12,880 --> 00:00:14,320
all names of the members of our Awakening Society

6
00:00:14,560 --> 00:00:15,360
will remain hidden from the public.

7
00:00:15,680 --> 00:00:17,040
So, we will draw from the pool

8
00:00:17,440 --> 00:00:18,400
to give each one a number

9
00:00:18,560 --> 00:00:20,240
as a code for communication,

10
00:00:20,400 --> 00:00:21,440
also as the pseudonym.

11
00:00:22,160 --> 00:00:24,880
There are fifty notes on the table now.

12
00:00:25,200 --> 00:00:26,880
A number is written on each note.

13
00:00:27,200 --> 00:00:28,480
The number you draw

14
00:00:28,720 --> 00:00:30,800
is your future correspondance code and pen name.

15
00:00:31,440 --> 00:00:32,720
Let's start now.

16
00:00:46,400 --> 00:00:47,360
I'm number 36.

17
00:00:47,680 --> 00:00:49,760
Then I will be called Shanlu from now on.

18
00:00:53,200 --> 00:00:55,840
I'm number one. My name wil be Yihao.

19
00:00:53,515 --> 00:00:55,887
[Deng Yingchao, Member of the Tianjin Awakening Society]

20
00:01:00,320 --> 00:01:01,120
I'm number five.

21
00:01:01,440 --> 00:01:03,200
I will be Wuhao.

22
00:01:05,600 --> 00:01:06,240
Comrades.

23
00:01:06,480 --> 00:01:08,480
The first activity organized by our Awakening Society.

24
00:01:08,640 --> 00:01:11,040
is to invite Professor Li Dazhao from Peking University

25
00:01:11,360 --> 00:01:13,920
to come here and give us lectures, guidance.

26
00:01:14,160 --> 00:01:16,560
Professor Li is the instructor of the May Fourth Movement in Beijing.

27
00:01:16,880 --> 00:01:18,240
He has rich experience.

28
00:01:18,640 --> 00:01:20,720
We should make full use of this opportunity,

29
00:01:21,280 --> 00:01:22,240
to learn as much as possible.

30
00:01:28,480 --> 00:01:29,200
Tell everyone,

31
00:01:28,885 --> 00:01:31,598
[Liu Residence, Luwan, Shanghai]

32
00:01:29,280 --> 00:01:31,280
the board meeting will be held at eight o'clock tomorrow.

33
00:01:31,920 --> 00:01:32,320
Yes.

34
00:01:38,560 --> 00:01:39,520
What's wrong?

35
00:01:40,720 --> 00:01:42,000
I can't stand it anymore.

36
00:01:42,800 --> 00:01:44,000
I have to go to Beijing.

37
00:01:44,320 --> 00:01:45,840
I'm bringing my little girl back whatever the cost.

38
00:01:48,080 --> 00:01:48,800
Calm down.

39
00:01:55,120 --> 00:01:55,680
Darling.

40
00:01:57,520 --> 00:02:00,400
The situation in Beijing is stable now.

41
00:02:00,640 --> 00:02:01,520
I believe

42
00:02:01,680 --> 00:02:02,880
she's safe in Beijing.

43
00:02:03,600 --> 00:02:06,960
Besides, our factory is now operating normally.

44
00:02:07,360 --> 00:02:08,400
It's a busy time.

45
00:02:09,200 --> 00:02:10,640
I thought they said

46
00:02:10,960 --> 00:02:12,480
that they will come back to Shanghai soon.

47
00:02:13,200 --> 00:02:14,960
Don't worry, when they get back to Shanghai

48
00:02:15,520 --> 00:02:17,600
I will figure out something to stop her from going to France.

49
00:02:19,920 --> 00:02:23,200
Wait, you won't let them go to France?

50
00:02:23,360 --> 00:02:23,680
No.

51
00:02:23,920 --> 00:02:26,160
So you're not interested in marrying our daughter into Chen's?

52
00:02:28,080 --> 00:02:29,600
Not to that family,

53
00:02:30,720 --> 00:02:31,760
with the dad going in and out jail.

54
00:02:32,800 --> 00:02:34,720
You were the one wanted that marriage.

55
00:02:35,040 --> 00:02:36,320
You said Chen Yannian has a bright future.

56
00:02:36,560 --> 00:02:37,680
He will be doing great things for the country.

57
00:02:38,240 --> 00:02:39,680
Things are different now.

58
00:02:40,720 --> 00:02:43,600
Throughout this May Fourth Movement,

59
00:02:44,000 --> 00:02:48,080
I realized a lot.

60
00:02:48,480 --> 00:02:49,680
This country

61
00:02:49,920 --> 00:02:52,880
is based on small-scale production and small-scale peasant economy.

62
00:02:53,280 --> 00:02:55,760
Once there is a large-scale movement from the bottom,

63
00:02:56,080 --> 00:02:58,240
it can be a disaster

64
00:02:58,640 --> 00:03:00,000
for people like us with assets and resources.

65
00:03:00,080 --> 00:03:02,000
I'm worring about our daughter.

66
00:03:02,160 --> 00:03:03,600
Why are you telling me these?

67
00:03:03,680 --> 00:03:05,840
I have to.

68
00:03:06,160 --> 00:03:07,440
Have you forgotten there's a time

69
00:03:07,920 --> 00:03:09,600
you couldn't sleep tight at all.

70
00:03:10,000 --> 00:03:12,720
You mean during the three strikes.

71
00:03:13,040 --> 00:03:14,320
Ah, at that time,

72
00:03:14,960 --> 00:03:16,800
schools and factories went on strike,

73
00:03:17,360 --> 00:03:18,240
businesses closed.

74
00:03:18,560 --> 00:03:19,760
Didn't all these three strikes

75
00:03:19,840 --> 00:03:20,800
happen here?

76
00:03:21,200 --> 00:03:22,000
That month,

77
00:03:22,240 --> 00:03:22,960
I did some calculations.

78
00:03:23,440 --> 00:03:25,840
We lost tens of thousands.

79
00:03:26,080 --> 00:03:27,760
Wasn't that strike opposing the Paris Peace Treaty?

80
00:03:27,840 --> 00:03:29,040
For patriotism and national salvation?

81
00:03:29,600 --> 00:03:30,480
You're not being patriotic now.

82
00:03:33,840 --> 00:03:34,640
Of course I'm patriotic.

83
00:03:35,520 --> 00:03:36,000
I am and

84
00:03:36,080 --> 00:03:37,760
I am more patriotic than those students.

85
00:03:37,920 --> 00:03:40,000
I believe in saving the nation through education,

86
00:03:40,880 --> 00:03:41,920
saving the country depends on industry.

87
00:03:42,240 --> 00:03:43,920
Anyway, I have no plan

88
00:03:44,480 --> 00:03:45,680
in becoming family with the Chen's.

89
00:03:46,000 --> 00:03:47,120
I can't take the risk.

90
00:03:48,720 --> 00:03:50,240
Say whatever you want, you are a businessman.

91
00:03:51,120 --> 00:03:51,920
When it comes to profits and ideals,

92
00:03:52,320 --> 00:03:53,520
it's always ideal for you.

93
00:04:05,120 --> 00:04:07,440
What is ideal?

94
00:04:08,160 --> 00:04:10,960
In my opinion, ideal is like a lamp.

95
00:04:11,680 --> 00:04:14,160
It lights up your heart.

96
00:04:14,480 --> 00:04:16,000
But if you really follow that light,

97
00:04:16,640 --> 00:04:18,080
you'll only fall and get injured.

98
00:04:19,120 --> 00:04:21,920
Moreover, there is no end.

99
00:04:24,000 --> 00:04:25,040
Whether this light

100
00:04:28,720 --> 00:04:31,200
will lead me to life or death,

101
00:04:32,480 --> 00:04:34,320
I have no idea.

102
00:04:38,409 --> 00:04:41,559
[Editorial Department of "New Youth"]

103
00:04:38,640 --> 00:04:39,520
Have some tea.

104
00:04:40,321 --> 00:04:41,559
[Chen Duxiu, styled Zhongfu, Professor at Peking University]

105
00:04:40,720 --> 00:04:41,440
Fellow colleagues.

106
00:04:41,920 --> 00:04:45,520
First of all, I'd like say I'm sorry.

107
00:04:45,812 --> 00:04:47,146
[Li Dazhao, styled Shouchang, Director of Peking University Library]
[Lu Xun, Civil servant under the Ministry of Education]

108
00:04:46,000 --> 00:04:46,960
Because of my arrest,

109
00:04:47,600 --> 00:04:49,120
"New Youth" has been on a pause for four months.

110
00:04:49,905 --> 00:04:50,721
Now,

111
00:04:51,360 --> 00:04:52,640
our readers

112
00:04:52,800 --> 00:04:53,840
and supporters

113
00:04:54,160 --> 00:04:55,920
have been calling for the restart of our paper.

114
00:04:56,320 --> 00:04:57,360
They all have high expectations.

115
00:04:57,760 --> 00:05:00,480
So today, we'll discuss this.

116
00:05:01,120 --> 00:05:03,280
After what happened,

117
00:05:03,680 --> 00:05:06,080
you must all have some special feelings.

118
00:05:07,040 --> 00:05:09,600
I hope you can share them with the others here.

119
00:05:12,693 --> 00:05:14,863
[Hu Shi, styled Shizhi, Professor at Peking University]

120
00:05:14,320 --> 00:05:15,120
Then I'll speak first.

121
00:05:16,160 --> 00:05:17,040
I think the biggest drawback

122
00:05:17,120 --> 00:05:18,160
of our paper

123
00:05:18,400 --> 00:05:19,760
is the rotating peer edit chief system.

124
00:05:20,000 --> 00:05:21,040
This system has forces

125
00:05:21,120 --> 00:05:22,560
every editor to only focus on what he wants.

126
00:05:23,040 --> 00:05:23,520
In a way,

127
00:05:23,600 --> 00:05:24,560
it stops our paper operating as a whole,

128
00:05:24,960 --> 00:05:26,000
and adds unpredictability to it.

129
00:05:26,560 --> 00:05:27,120
Shizhi.

130
00:05:28,000 --> 00:05:29,040
Whatever you say needs to be supported by evidence.

131
00:05:29,520 --> 00:05:31,200
Please give us an example.

132
00:05:31,600 --> 00:05:33,680
The example is lying around openly for everyone to see.

133
00:05:34,160 --> 00:05:35,120
We are discussing things here,

134
00:05:35,200 --> 00:05:36,480
and we must be right about things, not about people.

135
00:05:36,880 --> 00:05:39,200
Please, Mr. Bannong, don't take it personally.

136
00:05:39,600 --> 00:05:40,960
I have no intention of accusing you.

137
00:05:41,600 --> 00:05:43,600
What do you mean? Please speak out.

138
00:05:44,000 --> 00:05:45,200
If you insist,

139
00:05:45,680 --> 00:05:46,800
I'll speak my mind honestly then.

140
00:05:47,360 --> 00:05:49,280
For example, Shouchang was the editor on duty.

141
00:05:49,760 --> 00:05:51,280
He decided to put out an issue

142
00:05:51,440 --> 00:05:52,960
focusing on Marx's research.

143
00:05:53,280 --> 00:05:54,800
It received a lot of extreme comments

144
00:05:55,200 --> 00:05:55,920
and extreme feedback.

145
00:05:56,160 --> 00:05:57,280
It caused a lot of trouble.

146
00:05:57,680 --> 00:05:58,720
I think such an issue

147
00:05:58,880 --> 00:05:59,680
does not align with our beliefs

148
00:05:59,760 --> 00:06:01,200
in running this journal.

149
00:06:01,600 --> 00:06:02,080
Shizhi.

150
00:06:02,880 --> 00:06:03,440
During this period,

151
00:06:03,520 --> 00:06:05,600
you have been busy guesting Professor Dewey.

152
00:06:06,000 --> 00:06:07,360
There are many things you don't know.

153
00:06:08,080 --> 00:06:10,160
Shouchang didn't make that decision all by himself.

154
00:06:10,720 --> 00:06:12,480
That issue on research of Marxism,

155
00:06:12,720 --> 00:06:13,520
I knew about it.

156
00:06:14,080 --> 00:06:15,760
Deqian and Yucai also knew.

157
00:06:16,480 --> 00:06:17,040
Yes.

158
00:06:17,680 --> 00:06:18,960
The feedback and comments I have received,

159
00:06:19,120 --> 00:06:20,960
were mostly positive and of high recommendation

160
00:06:21,040 --> 00:06:22,640
from all walks of life.

161
00:06:23,200 --> 00:06:24,960
They said that this issue has brought a new trend

162
00:06:25,360 --> 00:06:26,720
for the research of ideology in China.

163
00:06:26,880 --> 00:06:28,880
That issue sold very well too.

164
00:06:28,960 --> 00:06:30,400
Many Japanese friends also wrote letters,

165
00:06:30,560 --> 00:06:32,080
saying they would like to take a look.

166
00:06:32,480 --> 00:06:33,600
Yes, yes, that issue

167
00:06:33,840 --> 00:06:35,040
was printed twice.

168
00:06:35,440 --> 00:06:36,880
There is not even one copy in stock now.

169
00:06:37,440 --> 00:06:39,280
It's not about how many copies been printed.

170
00:06:39,440 --> 00:06:40,880
When I took over the "Weekly Review",

171
00:06:41,200 --> 00:06:42,240
the circulation was also high.

172
00:06:42,480 --> 00:06:43,760
It still got banned at last.

173
00:06:43,951 --> 00:06:45,831
[Liu Bannong, Professor at Peking University]

174
00:06:44,480 --> 00:06:45,840
Then you should learn from your mistakes.

175
00:06:46,240 --> 00:06:46,560
Indeed.

176
00:06:46,960 --> 00:06:49,040
I learned the lesson.

177
00:06:49,440 --> 00:06:51,200
And I think this rotating editor-in-chief system

178
00:06:51,600 --> 00:06:53,040
is not necessary

179
00:06:53,200 --> 00:06:54,480
for our "New Youth".

180
00:06:54,800 --> 00:06:56,160
If you trust me,

181
00:06:56,400 --> 00:06:58,000
I will take the job as editor-in-chief.

182
00:06:58,320 --> 00:06:59,840
I will make sure that our "New Youth"

183
00:07:00,080 --> 00:07:02,240
becomes the foremost academic journal in China.

184
00:07:03,200 --> 00:07:04,160
Shizhi,

185
00:07:04,640 --> 00:07:07,680
you are still holding on your old mindset.

186
00:07:12,080 --> 00:07:13,280
Let me share my opinion.

187
00:07:14,080 --> 00:07:15,600
I agree that we should abolish the rotating system,

188
00:07:16,160 --> 00:07:18,960
no more people taking turns being the editor-in-chief.

189
00:07:19,760 --> 00:07:22,000
But I don't agree with Shizhi taking the job.

190
00:07:22,640 --> 00:07:23,360
Why?

191
00:07:23,680 --> 00:07:24,400
"New Youth"

192
00:07:24,960 --> 00:07:26,640
was brought to life by Zhongfu himself.

193
00:07:27,200 --> 00:07:28,720
Now that Zhongfu has been released,

194
00:07:29,120 --> 00:07:31,040
I think it should still be returned to Zhongfu.

195
00:07:31,360 --> 00:07:32,480
He can do the job.

196
00:07:32,640 --> 00:07:34,720
Zhongfu, you got this.

197
00:07:35,280 --> 00:07:36,800
We support you as always.

198
00:07:37,120 --> 00:07:38,160
I suggest,

199
00:07:38,320 --> 00:07:40,240
whoever supports this proposal please clap your hands.

200
00:07:40,640 --> 00:07:42,320
From Volume 7, Issue 1,

201
00:07:42,640 --> 00:07:44,320
"New Youth" will have Chen Duxiu as the editor-in-chief.

202
00:07:44,880 --> 00:07:45,280
Good.

203
00:07:52,320 --> 00:07:52,960
Good!

204
00:08:00,080 --> 00:08:01,120
Zhongfu tends to go to extremes.

205
00:08:01,680 --> 00:08:02,240
Why did you propose

206
00:08:02,320 --> 00:08:03,600
that he should do the job?

207
00:08:04,080 --> 00:08:05,520
Shizhi can be too cautious sometimes,

208
00:08:05,920 --> 00:08:06,800
but he is also careful.

209
00:08:07,120 --> 00:08:08,160
Things can't go too wrong if he is in charge.

210
00:08:09,360 --> 00:08:10,080
So you mean

211
00:08:10,160 --> 00:08:11,200
Shizhi should be editing "New Youth"

212
00:08:11,280 --> 00:08:12,240
by himself?

213
00:08:12,800 --> 00:08:14,080
I think he is more suitable than Zhongfu.

214
00:08:16,240 --> 00:08:17,040
Wrong.

215
00:08:17,840 --> 00:08:18,800
These two people,

216
00:08:19,760 --> 00:08:21,040
let me give you an analogy.

217
00:08:21,840 --> 00:08:24,960
If you see their strategy as a warehouse,

218
00:08:25,760 --> 00:08:28,640
Mr. Duxiu will set up a large banner in front of the door,

219
00:08:29,120 --> 00:08:30,160
with words written clearly on it:

220
00:08:30,640 --> 00:08:33,440
"Weaponed up, take care",

221
00:08:33,760 --> 00:08:34,800
but the door will be left open.

222
00:08:34,960 --> 00:08:36,480
You can know what is inside with one look, can be few knives or others.

223
00:08:36,560 --> 00:08:38,000
Open and clear, no need to worry.

224
00:08:38,560 --> 00:08:39,680
But when it comes to Mr. Shizhi,

225
00:08:40,240 --> 00:08:41,600
the warehouse will be closed

226
00:08:43,840 --> 00:08:45,200
with a small note on the door.

227
00:08:45,760 --> 00:08:46,800
Also with words written on it:

228
00:08:47,280 --> 00:08:50,560
"Nothing harmful inside, please don't be afraid".

229
00:08:51,120 --> 00:08:52,560
Of course this note could be telling the truth.

230
00:08:53,120 --> 00:08:55,040
But some people, at least people like me,

231
00:08:55,680 --> 00:08:56,720
I will always stop and think

232
00:08:56,800 --> 00:08:59,280
before I reach out and push that door.

233
00:08:59,920 --> 00:09:00,960
So you mean

234
00:09:01,840 --> 00:09:03,520
Zhongfu is more reliable, isn't it?

235
00:09:04,000 --> 00:09:05,200
Think for yourself.

236
00:09:08,000 --> 00:09:08,720
Obituary.

237
00:09:09,120 --> 00:09:11,760
Professor of Chinese Literature in Peking University,

238
00:09:12,080 --> 00:09:14,240
Instructor of the Faculty of Liberal Arts,

239
00:09:14,640 --> 00:09:17,920
Mr. Liu Shipei, Comptroller of National History Compilation Office,

240
00:09:18,640 --> 00:09:20,240
passed away of illness,

241
00:09:18,792 --> 00:09:21,463
[Cai Yuanpei, styled Jiemin, President of Peking University]

242
00:09:21,520 --> 00:09:23,200
at the age of 36.

243
00:09:23,840 --> 00:09:25,760
In memory of Professor Liu Shipei

244
00:09:26,080 --> 00:09:27,920
and his outstanding achievements in the many fields of

245
00:09:28,000 --> 00:09:30,080
classic studies, historiography and literature,

246
00:09:30,640 --> 00:09:33,360
a funeral ceremony for Professor Liu Shipei

247
00:09:33,760 --> 00:09:36,800
will be held today in Miaoguang Hall

248
00:09:37,520 --> 00:09:40,080
hosted by Mr. Chen Duxiu.

249
00:09:40,640 --> 00:09:44,480
Many students of the Chinese literature department,

250
00:09:45,200 --> 00:09:48,000
are invited to attend.

251
00:09:50,880 --> 00:09:51,520
This obituary,

252
00:09:53,440 --> 00:09:55,120
I'll have a student later

253
00:09:55,360 --> 00:09:57,040
posting this onto the bulletin board.

254
00:09:57,840 --> 00:10:01,520
Zhongfu, thank you for agreeing to host.

255
00:10:05,200 --> 00:10:06,240
I and Shenshu

256
00:10:08,320 --> 00:10:09,840
always had different political views,

257
00:10:11,200 --> 00:10:12,400
different academic views.

258
00:10:13,440 --> 00:10:14,240
But

259
00:10:14,800 --> 00:10:18,720
we did respect and value each other.

260
00:10:20,240 --> 00:10:22,960
It is also my wish to see him off.

261
00:10:26,640 --> 00:10:28,320
It's such a shame.

262
00:10:29,120 --> 00:10:30,160
Only thirty-six years old.

263
00:10:35,200 --> 00:10:38,720
What about the manuscripts of his works now?

264
00:10:39,760 --> 00:10:41,040
I organized a few people

265
00:10:41,600 --> 00:10:43,360
to check up and finish his manuscripts

266
00:10:44,320 --> 00:10:47,120
and give all those to Peking University Library for preservation.

267
00:10:47,600 --> 00:10:49,920
That will be my last work

268
00:10:50,800 --> 00:10:52,320
as the head of the compilation department

269
00:10:52,800 --> 00:10:56,560
at this job you assigned me to.

270
00:10:57,520 --> 00:11:00,320
Master Cai, I want to...

271
00:11:00,400 --> 00:11:01,040
Zhongfu.

272
00:11:02,560 --> 00:11:03,840
The thing is

273
00:11:04,400 --> 00:11:05,680
now that we lost Shenshu,

274
00:11:06,160 --> 00:11:07,440
the National History Compilation Office

275
00:11:07,520 --> 00:11:09,200
has lost its core.

